# Import Rules

## Absolute Imports Only

- Use absolute imports, NOT relative imports
- Paths are configured via tsconfig.json

```typescript
// Bad
import { Foo } from '../../components/Foo';
import { Bar } from './Bar';

// Good
import { Foo } from 'views/components/foo/foo.component';
import { Bar } from 'views/components/bar/bar.component';
```

## Type Imports

- Always use `import type` for type-only imports

```typescript
import type { IUserStore } from 'data/stores/user/user.store';
import { observer } from 'mobx-react';
```

## Lazy Loading for Pages

```typescript
const Home = lazy(retryFailLoad(() => import('views/pages/home/home.page')));
```

## Explicit Imports

- Import specific functions/components, not entire modules

```typescript
// Bad
import * as _ from 'lodash';

// Good
import { get, map } from 'lodash-es';
```

## No Duplicate Imports

- Each module should be imported only once per file
